<br>
We use a points as well, but not your usual DKP. Instead of assigning a point value to each item, each member who wants it sends a single tell with their bid to whichever officers happens to be running that raid. Highest bid wins, ties decided by the officer.<br>
<br>
Has the general advantage of making sure people are actually spending a decent amount of their points rather than just hoarding and bidding small amounts for each item. Since you can't see how many points other people are willing to spend when something drops... if you want it, you bid big and start racking up the points again through more raids.<br>
<br>
Helps distribute the loot a little more evenly across all our active raiding members than some other systems we've talked about. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=573077" target="_blank">Fvighlander</a><br>
